data.description: I'm all for people who are legitimately trying to learn about Japanese culture. If you're being respectful about it and genuinely want to learn, I'll teach you everything. I don't think those people are weeaboos... But if you go and act like you already know it all and pretend to be an expert when nearly everything you say is wrong, and you don't even know how to pronounce "desu" properly, I'm only going to teach you how to get your ass kicked if you ever go to Japan.
